<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9846&amp;p=110211#p110211"><![CDATA[
The displayed APU pitch register values in NSFPlay 2.2 are actually incorrect (of by one, I think). If you want a more accurate display use the <a href="https://dl.dropbox.com/u/883356/nsfplay23b2.zip" class="postlink">NSFPlay 2.3 beta</a>. Also the correct behaviour of $4017 was not emulated at all until the 2.3 beta. The actually sweep function I think was correct in 2.2, if I recall, but the lack of $4017 control means Zelda II still had some timing errors and might sound incorrect as well. (TLDR: Get the 2.3 beta if you're not using it already.)<br /><br />At any rate, the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU" class="postlink">APU info on the wiki</a> should be correct at this point. If you find it doesn't explain how the sweep works with enough detail, I'd like some feedback on that so I can revise it to be clearer.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Tue Mar 26, 2013 10:40 pm</p><hr />
