<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9846&amp;p=110201#p110201"><![CDATA[
If you're using FCEUX, the display there &quot;helpfully&quot; indicates the value read from memory at that location (which is open bus), not the value you will write, the value in apu register, or anything else more useful.<br /><br />So when you set a breakpoint of &quot;$4001 != $FF&quot;, you get what blargg said. You'll want something more like &quot;break on writes of $4001 where A != $FF&quot; and then you get to hope that they used STA to write to the register instead of STX or STY.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Tue Mar 26, 2013 6:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
